Import sq objects from other objects

Source: R/import_sq.R
import_sq.Rd

Creates sq object from object of class from another package. Currently supported packages are ape with its formats (AAbin and DNAbin), Bioconductor (AAStringSet, DNAStringSet) and seqinr (SeqFastaAA, SeqFastadna).

import_sq(object)

Arguments

object

- an object of one of classes: AAbin, DNAbin, AAStringSet, DNAStringSet, SeqFastaAA, SeqFastadna.

Value

A tibble with sq column of sq type representing the same sequences as given object; the object has a type corresponding to the input type; if given sequences had names, output tibble has also another column name with those names

Details

Providing object of class other than specified will result in error.

See also

export_sq sq

Examples

## ape example
library(ape)
#> 
#> Attaching package: ‘ape’
#> The following object is masked from ‘package:tidysq’:
#> 
#>     complement
ape_dna <- as.DNAbin(list(one = c("C", "T", "C", "A"), two = c("T", "G", "A", "G", "G")))
import_sq(ape_dna)
#> # A tibble: 2 x 2
#>   name  sq       
#>   <chr> <(c)dna> 
#> 1 one   CTCA  <4>
#> 2 two   TGAGG <5>

## seqinr example
library(seqinr)
#> 
#> Attaching package: ‘seqinr’
#> The following object is masked from ‘package:Biostrings’:
#> 
#>     translate
#> The following objects are masked from ‘package:ape’:
#> 
#>     as.alignment, consensus
seqinr_dna <- as.SeqFastadna(list(one = c("C", "T", "C", "A"), 
                                  two = c("T", "G", "A", "G", "G")))
import_sq(seqinr_dna)
#> # A tibble: 2 x 1
#>   sq       
#>   <(c)dna> 
#> 1 CTCA  <4>
#> 2 TGAGG <5>
